`screen.css:2273-2289`:
```
.gh-content :not(.kg-card):not(table):not([id]) + :is(.kg-card, table) { margin-top: …}
.gh-content :is(.kg-card, table) + :not(.kg-card):not(table):not([id]) { margin-top: …}
.gh-content :not(.kg-card):not([id]) + .kg-card.kg-width-full { margin-top: …}
.gh-content .kg-card.kg-width-full + :not(.kg-card):not([id]) { margin-top: …}
```
If our renderer emits a card NOT directly under `.gh-content` (e.g. wraps it in a `<div class="nectar-card">`), every spacing rule fails. If the card has a `[id]` (e.g. from `marked-gfm-heading-id` accidentally tagging it), spacing rules also miss.

**Fix**: post-process pass enforces `.kg-card` elements as direct children of `.gh-content` and never carry an `[id]` attribute the heading-id plugin would assign. Add a snapshot test.

engine.ts:138 sets `member: undefined`. That's fine for `{{#if @member}}` (falsy → ok). But `{{@member.email}}` or `{{#each @member.subscriptions}}` in some themes crashes Handlebars with `Cannot read properties of undefined`.

Fix: set `@member` to a frozen sentinel object whose getter returns `undefined` for any property and an empty array for known collections. Example:
```ts
const memberStub = new Proxy({}, {
  get: (_, key) => {
    if (key === 'subscriptions' || key === 'tiers') return [];
    if (key === 'paid' || key === 'comped') return false;
    return undefined;
  },
});
```
Document: `@member` is *always* truthy-stub-aware; templates that branch on `{{#if @member}}` still see `false` because Proxy with no values is truthy. So leave the sentinel undefined for `#if` and add a separate `@_member` for nested access — or, simpler, recommend themes use `{{#if @member}}` only, and stub nested access via a guarded helper.

Ghost's `{{price tier currencyCode="USD"}}` outputs `$9` / `$90` formatted with locale-aware currency. Themes use it heavily on pricing pages. Implement as:
```ts
hb.registerHelper('price', (tier, opts) => {
  const cents = tier?.monthly_price ?? 0;
  return new Intl.NumberFormat(opts.hash.locale ?? siteLocale, {
    style: 'currency',
    currency: opts.hash.currencyCode ?? 'USD',
  }).format(cents / 100);
});
```
Note: Ghost stores prices in cents. Be explicit in docs about the unit.
